description:
The Moroccan authorities announced the 23rd of April 2020  in the context of the "state of health emergency" a "Night movement ban" from the 1st Ramadan/ Saturday 25th April from 7 PM to 5 AM, giving the exception to: 
-Medics and paramedics;
-Public authorities, army forces, and police;
-People with medical emergencies;
-Night workers with a proof certificate from their institutions;
-Religious curators charged with raising the call to prayer in mosques.

